    "source": "75a397eb-8bc4-4cf8-bbc8-d248d23925ea.pdf_page_221",
    "contenu": "The document presents an aroma profile for raw beetroot. Below, you will find the content organized in a structured format.\n\n### Raw Beetroot Aroma Profile\n\n#### Overview\nThe aroma profile of beetroot is made up of more than just geosmin. It contains peachy and pineapple-scented lactones, which reportedly goes best with fruits like apricots and figs to bring out those fruity notes. Beetroot also exhibits a floral scent similar to that of apples, in addition to pyrazines that give it an earthy, musty flavor. This profile can blend well with various foods, including carrots, parsnips, quinoa, and horseradish.\n\n#### Aromas Identified in Beetroot\n- **Peach**\n- **Pineapple**\n- **Green**\n- **Earthy**\n- **Musty**\n- **Floral** (similar to apple)\n\n### Visualization\nThe image includes a circular aroma chart that visually represents the various scents associated with raw beetroot. The circle is segmented into sections such as earthy, musty, floral, and others, with converging lines pointing toward the center.\n\n### Beetroot Pairing Chart\nBelow is a structured representation of the beetroot pairing chart.\n\n| Ingredient | Butter | Soy Sauce | Mustard | Vinegar | Cocoa | Coffee | Vanilla | Honey | Truffle Oil | Grilled |\n|------------|--------|-----------|---------|---------|-------|--------|---------|-------|-------------|---------|\n| Beetroot   | ●      | ●         | ●       | ●       | ●     | ●      | o       | ●     | o           | o       |\n| Dried Cherry Blossom | ●      |           |         |         |       |        |         |       |             |         |\n| Roasted Prawns |         | ●         |         |         |       |        |         |       |             |      ●   |\n| Passion Fruit | ●      |           |         |         |       |        |         | ●     |             |         |\n| Iberian Ham (100% Ibérico de Bellota) |         |           |         |         |       |        |         |       |             |     