    "contenu": "The document covers various tools used in fermentation processes. Here is the detailed structured content of it:\n\n---\n\n### Hydrometers\nHydrometers are instruments used to measure the specific gravity of a solution, which is the ratio of the density of the solution to the density of water. This measurement can provide insights into the alcohol potential of the solution and whether any unfermented sugar remains. The document mentions that although hydrometers are rarely used by the author in mead fermentation, they are popular among many home fermenters for being cost-effective and simple to use.\n\n### Thermometers\nThermometers are crucial in many fermentation processes, particularly for maintaining specific temperature ranges or cooling ingredients. The document mentions two types of thermometers:\n1. **Dial Thermometer:** Commonly found and used for general purposes.\n2. **Digital Thermometer with a cord:** This type includes a sensor attached by a cord, similar to a meat thermometer with a readout external to the device it measures. Particularly useful for monitoring temperatures in incubation chambers without opening them, which helps maintain the internal temperature by preventing external air exposure.\n\n### Cider and Grape Presses\nThis section heading is visible at the bottom of the document; however, the actual content related to cider and grape presses is not shown in the provided image.\n\n---\n\nThe text suggests practical applications and gives personal insights on the utility of these tools, like the minimal use of hydrometers by the author and the specific use of a cabled digital thermometer for incubation purposes."
