    "contenu": "Here is the structured content extracted from the provided document:\n\n---\n\n### Recipe: Lamb Stew with a Mediterranean Twist\n\n#### Ingredients:\n- Olive oil\n- Lamb\n- Salt and pepper\n- Onions\n- Garlic\n- Cumin\n- Paprika\n- Wine\n- Tomato paste\n- Stock\n- Red pepper strips\n- Parsley and olives for garnish\n\n#### Instructions:\n1. **Preparation**: In a large sauté pan, heat 1/4 cup of the olive oil over high heat. Sprinkle lamb with salt and pepper, and cook in batches until brown. \n2. **Cooking**: Transfer lamb to a large pot. Sauté onions and garlic in the same pan. Add spices and continue to cook. Mix onion mixture with lamb, add wine, stock, and tomato paste. Bring to gentle boil and simmer until lamb is tender.\n3. **Garnishing**: Add red pepper strips, simmer briefly, and season to taste. Garnish the stew with chopped parsley and olives.\n\n#### Cooking Tip:\n- Adjust the amount of tomato paste based on the dryness or sweetness of the wine used in cooking.\n\n#### Commentary:\n- Meat and sweet peppers paired with pungent seasonings offer a traditional Mediterranean flavor.\n- Roasted peppers are a good match with oaky wines, enhancing the smokiness in the dish.\n\n---\n\n### Recommended Cabernet Sauvignon Producers and Their Styles:\n\n#### Everyday Wines:\n1. **Wolf Blass** _(Multiple appellations, South Australia)_\n2. **Gallo of Sonoma** _(Sonoma County, California)_\n3. **Estancia** _(Sonoma/Central Coast, California)_\n\n#### Premium Wines:\n1. **Geyser Peak** _(Sonoma County, California)_\n2. **Provenance** _(Napa Valley, California)_\n3. **Silverado Vineyards** _(Napa Valley, California)_\n\n#### Splurge Wines:\n1. **Shafer** _(Napa Valley, California)_\n2. **Miner Family** _(Napa Valley, California)_\n3. **Joseph Phelps** _(Napa Valley, California)_\n\nThis document includes a lamb stew recipe with suggestions on wine pairing and lists of recommended Cabernet Sauvignon wine producers categorized by everyday, premium, and splurge options."
